abstract: A finding by the Federal Trade Commission that Google had not broken the law by highlighting its own services in search results could strengthen the firm’s already dominant position.
snippet: A finding by the Federal Trade Commission that Google had not broken the law by highlighting its own services in search results could strengthen the firm’s already dominant position.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission on Thursday handed Google a major victory by declaring, after an investigation of nearly two years, that the company had not violated antitrust or anticompetition statutes in the way it arranges its Web search results.

headline.main: A Victory for Google as F.T.C. Takes No Formal Steps
headline.print_headline: U.S. Ends Inquiry On Web Search; Google Is Victor
